parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light stays on
the brakes engage unnecessarily
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes make a grinding or loud noise
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes make a grinding or loud noise
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Accelerator Pedal Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal and accelerator pedal can cause the driver's foot to become wedged between the two pedals, making it difficult and unsafe to drive.
symptoms: The driver's foot becomes wedged between the brake pedal and accelerator pedal
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Warning Light Malfunctions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals and warning lights can cause confusion and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The turn signals do not work
the warning sound for the headlights being left on when the door is open does not work
the warning sound for the driver's seatbelt does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slow movement of the power windows can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The power windows move slowly up and down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defects in the tires can cause loss of control, accidents, or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The tires have slow leaks
the tires are defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front torsion bar can cause the front end of the vehicle to drop, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle drops
the vehicle vibrates at high speeds
the steering shakes
the vehicle is difficult to control
the front suspension collapses
and the vehicle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear springs can cause an unstable condition while driving at high speeds, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's body is not properly supported
and the vehicle may drop onto the frame at any time
causing an unstable condition.
